Cell B20 | value='The depth of the apparent redox potential discontinuity (aRPD) in 2008, or the change in sediment color from oxidized (reddish/brown/tan) to reduced (black). The aRPD depth represents the recent history of bottom-water oxygen concentrations and bioturbation/irrigation. In Narragansett Bay, the aRPD depth is responsive to oxygen concentrations between 14-28 days prior to image collection. The maximum aRPD depth of any station replicate was used to represent the station. NA: Station not sampled and/or no images obtained from station and/or images missing from the archive, preventing reanalysis. indet: Images were collected but not interpretable for aRPD depth.' | fill=00000000 | rows=[19] | cols=[1] | col_header=False | row_header=False | metadata=False
